skGeMibVersion.name: skGeMibVersion
skGeMibVersion.description: The version of this MIB (e.g. v1.0).

skGeAction.name: skGeAction
skGeAction.description: Returns on query 'idle'. A set to 'idle' does nothing. A set to 'force-trap' transmits the trap specified in skGeTrapForceType. 'save-permanent' saves the setable values of this MIB permanently.

skGeTable.name: skGeTable
skGeTable.description: Table for general adapter specific information.

skGeIfIndex.name: skGeIfIndex
skGeIfIndex.description: Stores the corresponding ifIndex of the mib-2 interfaces table. If the value cannot be obtained a '0' is stored.

skGeDeviceType.name: skGeDeviceType
skGeDeviceType.description: Returns the object identifier of the NIC. If it is unknown 0.0 is returned.

skGeDriverDescr.name: skGeDriverDescr
skGeDriverDescr.description: A description of the driver (e.g. sk98win - Miniport Gigabit-Ethernet driver).

skGeHwDescr.name: skGeHwDescr
skGeHwDescr.description: A description of the device hardware (e.g. SK-NET Genesis Sx Single Port).

skGeChipSet.name: skGeChipSet
skGeChipSet.description: Stores the object identifier of the used chip-set.

skGeDeviceAction.name: skGeDeviceAction
skGeDeviceAction.description: A set to this variable performs a specific action. A get-request to this variable always returns the idle (1) value. The result of the self-test is stored in skGeTestResult.

skGeTestResult.name: skGeTestResult
skGeTestResult.description: Stores the self test result, which was initiated by skGeDeviceAction. The value is a sum and 2 raised the power of the result is added to the sum. A sum of zero indicates a successful self-test. Result Power unkown 0 (Initial value) tranceiverErr 1 asicErr 2 sensorErr 3 powermgmtErr 4 pciErr 5 macErr 6

skGeBusSpeed.name: skGeBusSpeed
skGeBusSpeed.description: Returns the bus speed in MHz (e.g. 33 means a bus speed of 33 MHz). If the value is unknown a 0 is returned.

skGeBusWidth.name: skGeBusWidth
skGeBusWidth.description: Returns the bus width in bits (e.g. 64 means a bus width of 64 bit). If the value is unknown a 0 is returned.

skGeChecksumTable.name: skGeChecksumTable
skGeChecksumTable.description: Table of the adapter hardware checksumming module.

skGeChecksumIndex.name: skGeChecksumIndex
skGeChecksumIndex.description: Index of the protocol. The indexes have fixed semantics.

skGeChecksumRxOkCts.name: skGeChecksumRxOkCts
skGeChecksumRxOkCts.description: Number of received frames for which the protocol checksum verification was successfully performed in hardware.

skGeChecksumRxUnableCts.name: skGeChecksumRxUnableCts
skGeChecksumRxUnableCts.description: Number of received frames for which the protocol checksum verification was left to the protocol.

skGeChecksumRxErrCts.name: skGeChecksumRxErrCts
skGeChecksumRxErrCts.description: Number of received frames for which the protocol checksum verification in hardware found an error.

skGeChecksumTxOkCts.name: skGeChecksumTxOkCts
skGeChecksumTxOkCts.description: Number of transmitted packets for which the protocol checksum was generated in hardware.

skGeChecksumTxUnableCts.name: skGeChecksumTxUnableCts
skGeChecksumTxUnableCts.description: Number of packets, which could not be sent because the requested generation of the checksum was not possible.

skGeTrapForceType.name: skGeTrapForceType
skGeTrapForceType.description: Stores the trap number and the value list that is to be transmitted. The transmission is initiated with skGeAction (force-trap). Each field in the octet string consists of a one octet length field followed by the value.

skGeTrapDestTable.name: skGeTrapDestTable
skGeTrapDestTable.description: Table of trap destination addresses to which the agent will send traps.

skGeTrapDestIndex.name: skGeTrapDestIndex
skGeTrapDestIndex.description: Index of the trap destination table.

skGeTrapDestAddress.name: skGeTrapDestAddress
skGeTrapDestAddress.description: The destination address to which the agent sends its trap PDUs.

skGeTrapFilter.name: skGeTrapFilter
skGeTrapFilter.description: The trap filter bits are stored as a sum of powers of 2 (a bit string) in this variable. If the bit is set to 0 the corresponding trap will not be transmitted. If the bit is set to 1 trap transmission is enabled. Trap Power skGeSensorWarningLower 0 skGeSensorWarningUpper 1 skGeSensorErrorLower 2 skGeSensorErrorUpper 3 skGeRlmtChangeThresholdCondition 4 skGeRlmtChangeCondition 5 skGeRlmtPortDown 6 skGeRlmtPortUp 7 skGeRlmtSegmentation 8

skGeSensorGeIndex.name: skGeSensorGeIndex
skGeSensorGeIndex.description: Adapter index which corresponds with skGeIndex.

skGeSensorIndex.name: skGeSensorIndex
skGeSensorIndex.description: Index of the sensor. The indexes have fixed semantics.

skGeSensorDescr.name: skGeSensorDescr
skGeSensorDescr.description: A textual description of the sensor.

skGeSensorValue.name: skGeSensorValue
skGeSensorValue.description: Stores the current value of the sensor in 10th of degree celsius, milli volts or round per minutes (rpm).

skGeSensorWarningThresholdLow.name: skGeSensorWarningThresholdLow
skGeSensorWarningThresholdLow.description: Stores the lower warning threshold of the allowed value range for the monitored unit.

skGeSensorWarningThresholdHigh.name: skGeSensorWarningThresholdHigh
skGeSensorWarningThresholdHigh.description: Stores the upper warning threshold of the allowed value range for the monitored unit.

skGeSensorErrorThresholdLow.name: skGeSensorErrorThresholdLow
skGeSensorErrorThresholdLow.description: Stores the lower threshold of the allowed value range for the monitored unit.

skGeSensorErrorThresholdHigh.name: skGeSensorErrorThresholdHigh
skGeSensorErrorThresholdHigh.description: Stores the upper threshold of the allowed value range for the monitored unit.

skGeSensorStatus.name: skGeSensorStatus
skGeSensorStatus.description: If a threshold is exceeded this flag will be set.

skGeSensorWarningCts.name: skGeSensorWarningCts
skGeSensorWarningCts.description: If a warning threshold is exceeded this counter will be incremented and a trap will be generated. If the sensor value exceeds the threshold permanently this counter is incremented every two seconds and a trap is generated.

skGeSensorErrorCts.name: skGeSensorErrorCts
skGeSensorErrorCts.description: If a threshold is exceeded this counter will be incremented and a trap will be generated. If the sensor value exceeds the threshold permanently this counter is incremented every second and a trap is generated.

skGeSensorWarningTimeStamp.name: skGeSensorWarningTimeStamp
skGeSensorWarningTimeStamp.description: Stores the time since the last reboot in hundreds of seconds of the last warning threshold exceed.

skGeSensorErrorTimeStamp.name: skGeSensorErrorTimeStamp
skGeSensorErrorTimeStamp.description: Stores the time since the last reboot in hundreds of seconds of the last error threshold exceed.

skGeStatEntriesNumber.name: skGeStatEntriesNumber
skGeStatEntriesNumber.description: Number of entries in the skGeStatTable.

skGeStatTable.name: skGeStatTable
skGeStatTable.description: Statistical data of the ports. The number of table entries is stored in skGeStatEntriesNumber.

skGeStatEntry.name: skGeStatEntry
skGeStatEntry.description: The first entry (skGeStatIndex) of each adapter card (skGeStatGeIndex) is a virtual one and represents the currently active port with settled statistical data. This means that the number of port specific statistical data entries in this table is by one element higher than the physically provided port number (skGePortNumber).

skGeStatGeIndex.name: skGeStatGeIndex
skGeStatGeIndex.description: Adapter index which corresponds with skGeIndex.

skGeStatIndex.name: skGeStatIndex
skGeStatIndex.description: The port index. The first index denotes the virtual port entry, which contains settled statistical data. The ports are enumerated from 1..n.

skGeStatTxOkCts.name: skGeStatTxOkCts
skGeStatTxOkCts.description: A count of frames (including short frames, broadcasts frames, and multicast frames) that are successfully transmitted.

skGeStatTxOctetsHighOkCts.name: skGeStatTxOctetsHighOkCts
skGeStatTxOctetsHighOkCts.description: The upper 32 bit count of data and padding octets of frames that are successfully transmitted.

skGeStatTxOctetsLowOkCts.name: skGeStatTxOctetsLowOkCts
skGeStatTxOctetsLowOkCts.description: The lower 32 bit count of data and padding octets of frames that are successfully transmitted.

skGeStatTxBroadcastOkCts.name: skGeStatTxBroadcastOkCts
skGeStatTxBroadcastOkCts.description: A count of frames that were successfully transmitted to the broadcast address. Frames transmitted to multicast addresses are not broadcast frames and are excluded.

skGeStatTxMulticastOkCts.name: skGeStatTxMulticastOkCts
skGeStatTxMulticastOkCts.description: A count of frames that were successfully transmitted to a group destination address other than broadcast.

skGeStatTxUnicastOkCts.name: skGeStatTxUnicastOkCts
skGeStatTxUnicastOkCts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were directed to an unicast address. This number does not include frames directed to broadcast or multicast addresses.

skGeStatTxLongFramesCts.name: skGeStatTxLongFramesCts
skGeStatTxLongFramesCts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that are more than the IEEE 802.3 maximum frame size. Typically, 1518 octets if neither the OneLevelVLAN nor TwoLevelVLAN is active, the long frames are defined as more than 1522 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). If the TowLevelVLAN is active, then long frames are defined as more than 1538 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxBurstCts.name: skGeStatTxBurstCts
skGeStatTxBurstCts.description: The total number of burst events.

skGeStatTxPFlowCtrlCts.name: skGeStatTxPFlowCtrlCts
skGeStatTxPFlowCtrlCts.description: The total number of Pause Flow-Control frames transmitted, of Opcode=0001.

skGeStatTxFlowCtrlCts.name: skGeStatTxFlowCtrlCts
skGeStatTxFlowCtrlCts.description: A count of Flow Control frames transmitted.

skGeStatTxSingleCollisionsCts.name: skGeStatTxSingleCollisionsCts
skGeStatTxSingleCollisionsCts.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision.

skGeStatTxMultipleCollisionsCts.name: skGeStatTxMultipleCollisionsCts
skGeStatTxMultipleCollisionsCts.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision.

skGeStatTxExcessiveCollisionsCts.name: skGeStatTxExcessiveCollisionsCts
skGeStatTxExcessiveCollisionsCts.description: A count of frames that due to excessive collisions are not transmitted successfully.

skGeStatTxLateCollisionsCts.name: skGeStatTxLateCollisionsCts
skGeStatTxLateCollisionsCts.description: A count of the times that a collision has been detected later than one slot time, from the start of the packet transmission. A late collision is counted twice, i.e., both as a collision and as a lateCollision.

skGeStatTxDeferralCts.name: skGeStatTxDeferralCts
skGeStatTxDeferralCts.description: A count of frames whose transmission was delayed on its first attempt because the medium was busy.

skGeStatTxExcessiveDeferralCts.name: skGeStatTxExcessiveDeferralCts
skGeStatTxExcessiveDeferralCts.description: A count of frames that deferred for an excessive period of time. This counter may only be incremented once per LLC transmission.

skGeStatTxFifoUnderrunCts.name: skGeStatTxFifoUnderrunCts
skGeStatTxFifoUnderrunCts.description: The number of transmit FIFO underrun events.

skGeStatTxCarrierSenseCts.name: skGeStatTxCarrierSenseCts
skGeStatTxCarrierSenseCts.description: A count of times that the carrier sense condition was not asserted or was deasserted during the transmission of a frame without collision.

skGeStatTxOctets64Cts.name: skGeStatTxOctets64Cts
skGeStatTxOctets64Cts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxOctets127Cts.name: skGeStatTxOctets127Cts
skGeStatTxOctets127Cts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxOctets255Cts.name: skGeStatTxOctets255Cts
skGeStatTxOctets255Cts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxOctets511Cts.name: skGeStatTxOctets511Cts
skGeStatTxOctets511Cts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxOctets1023Cts.name: skGeStatTxOctets1023Cts
skGeStatTxOctets1023Cts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxOctetsMaxCts.name: skGeStatTxOctetsMaxCts
skGeStatTxOctetsMaxCts.description: The total number of frames transmitted that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). If the OneLevelVLAN is active this statistic counts frames that are between 1024 and 1522 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). If the TwoLevelVLAN is active, this statistic counts the frames that are between 1024 and 1538 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeStatTxSyncCts.name: skGeStatTxSyncCts
skGeStatTxSyncCts.description: The total number of frames transmitted synchronuously.

skGeStatTxSyncOctetsHighCts.name: skGeStatTxSyncOctetsHighCts
skGeStatTxSyncOctetsHighCts.description: The upper 32 bit count of synchronuously transmitted octets.

skGeStatTxSyncOctetsLowCts.name: skGeStatTxSyncOctetsLowCts
skGeStatTxSyncOctetsLowCts.description: The lower 32 bit count of synchronuously transmitted octets.

skGeStatRxOkCts.name: skGeStatRxOkCts
skGeStatRxOkCts.description: A count of frames (including short frames, broadcast frames, and multicast frames) that are successfully received.

skGeStatRxOctetsHighOkCts.name: skGeStatRxOctetsHighOkCts
skGeStatRxOctetsHighOkCts.description: The upper 32 bit count of data and padding octets in frames that are successfully received. This does not include octets in frames received with frame-too-long, FCS, length or alignment errors, or frames lost due to internal MAC sub-layer error.

skGeStatRxOctetsLowOkCts.name: skGeStatRxOctetsLowOkCts
skGeStatRxOctetsLowOkCts.description: The lower 32 bit count of data and padding octets in frames that are successfully received. This does not include octets in frames received with frame-too-long, FCS, length or alignment errors, or frames lost due to internal MAC sub-layer error.

skGeStatRxBroadcastOkCts.name: skGeStatRxBroadcastOkCts
skGeStatRxBroadcastOkCts.description: A count of frames that are successfully received and are directed to the broadcast group address. This does not include frames received with frame-too-long, FCS, length or alignment errors, or frames lost due to internal MAC sub-layer error.

skGeStatRxMulticastOkCts.name: skGeStatRxMulticastOkCts
skGeStatRxMulticastOkCts.description: A count of frames that are successfully received and are directed to an active non-broadcast group address. This does not include frames received with frame-too- long, FCS, length or alignment errors, or frames lost due to internal MAC sub-layer error.

skGeStatRxUnicastOkCts.name: skGeStatRxUnicastOkCts
skGeStatRxUnicastOkCts.description: The total number of good frames received that were directed to any unicast address, as defined by the Counter Exact Address Match Criteria.

skGeStatRxPFlowCtrlCts.name: skGeStatRxPFlowCtrlCts
skGeStatRxPFlowCtrlCts.description: A count of Flow Control frames received with a length- or-type field value equal to the reserved type for 802.3_MAC_Control and an opcode indicating a PAUSE operation.

skGeStatRxFlowCtrlCts.name: skGeStatRxFlowCtrlCts
skGeStatRxFlowCtrlCts.description: A count of Flow Control frames received. Flow Control frames are defined as valid frames with a length-or-type field value equal to the reserved type for 802.3_MAC_Control.

skGeStatRxPFlowCtrlErrCts.name: skGeStatRxPFlowCtrlErrCts
skGeStatRxPFlowCtrlErrCts.description: A count of Flow Control frames received with standard PAUSE address with a length-or-type field value equal to the reserved type for 802.3_MAC_Control, but without a valid PAUSE Opcode (0001).

skGeStatRxFlowCtrlUnknownCts.name: skGeStatRxFlowCtrlUnknownCts
skGeStatRxFlowCtrlUnknownCts.description: A count of Flow Control frames received that contain an opcode that is not supported by the device. Flow Control frames are defined as valid frames with a length-or-type field value equal to the reserved type for 802.3_MAC_Control and with an opcode for a function that is not supported by the device.

skGeStatRxBurstCts.name: skGeStatRxBurstCts
skGeStatRxBurstCts.description: The total number of burst events.

skGeStatRxMissedCts.name: skGeStatRxMissedCts
skGeStatRxMissedCts.description: The total number of events in which frames were missed by the controller due to buffer overflow.

skGeStatRxFramingCts.name: skGeStatRxFramingCts
skGeStatRxFramingCts.description: The total number of frames received with improper end- of-frame delimiter

skGeStatRxFifoOverflowCts.name: skGeStatRxFifoOverflowCts
skGeStatRxFifoOverflowCts.description: The number of receive FIFO overflow events.

skGeStatRxJabberCts.name: skGeStatRxJabberCts
skGeStatRxJabberCts.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets), and had a bad FCS with an integral number of octets; 1522 octets if OneLevelVLAN is active; 1538 octets if TwoLeveVLAN is active.

skGeStatRxCarrierCts.name: skGeStatRxCarrierCts
skGeStatRxCarrierCts.description: An event counter for the number of times the carrier event is longer than the permissible duration.

skGeStatRxIRLengthCts.name: skGeStatRxIRLengthCts
skGeStatRxIRLengthCts.description: A count of frames with a length-or-type field value between the minimum unpadded LLC MAC client data size and the maximum allowed LLC MAC client data size inclusive, that does not match the number of LLC MAC client data octets received. The counter also contains frames with a length-or-type field value less than the minimum unpadded LLC MAC client data size. Note: this error is not generated if length field is between 1 and 45 (as this becomes padding case).

skGeStatRxSymbolCts.name: skGeStatRxSymbolCts
skGeStatRxSymbolCts.description: A count of the number of times the receiving media is non-idle (a carrier event) for a period of time greater than or equal to slot-time for half-duplex operation, or greater than or equal to min-frame-size for full-duplex operation, and during which there was at least one occurrence of an event that causes the PHY to indicate 'Data reception error' on the GMII.

skGeStatRxShortsCts.name: skGeStatRxShortsCts
skGeStatRxShortsCts.description: An event counter by one for each carrier event with activity-duration less than short-event-max-time. In the 1000 Mb/s case short-event-max-time is 72 bits (9 octets).

skGeStatRxRuntCts.name: skGeStatRxRuntCts
skGeStatRxRuntCts.description: A counter for each carrier-event that the octet count is less than 64.

skGeStatRxCextCts.name: skGeStatRxCextCts
skGeStatRxCextCts.description: A counter of received frames with no collision, short, or framing error in which the carrier extension was inadequate.

skGeStatRxTooLongCts.name: skGeStatRxTooLongCts
skGeStatRxTooLongCts.description: A count of frames received that exceed the maximum permitted frame size, i.e., 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. The maximum frame length could be 1522 octets if OneLevelVLAN is active or 1538 octets if TwoLevelVLAN is active.

skGeStatRxFCSCts.name: skGeStatRxFCSCts
skGeStatRxFCSCts.description: A count of received frames that are an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. This does not include frames received with frame-too-long, or frame-too-short (frame fragment) error.

skGeStatRxOctets64Cts.name: skGeStatRxOctets64Cts
skGeStatRxOctets64Cts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets).

skGeStatRxOctets127Cts.name: skGeStatRxOctets127Cts
skGeStatRxOctets127Cts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets).

skGeStatRxOctets255Cts.name: skGeStatRxOctets255Cts
skGeStatRxOctets255Cts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets).

skGeStatRxOctets511Cts.name: skGeStatRxOctets511Cts
skGeStatRxOctets511Cts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets).

skGeStatRxOctets1023Cts.name: skGeStatRxOctets1023Cts
skGeStatRxOctets1023Cts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets).

skGeStatRxOctetsMaxCts.name: skGeStatRxOctetsMaxCts
skGeStatRxOctetsMaxCts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets). If the OneLevelVLAN is active, this statistic counts frames that are between 1024 and 1522 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets). If the TwoLevelVLAN is active, this statistic counts frames that are between 1024 and 1538 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets).

skGeStatRxLongFramesCts.name: skGeStatRxLongFramesCts
skGeStatRxLongFramesCts.description: The total number of frames received that are greater than the IEEE 802.3 maximum frame size. Typically, 1518 octets if neither the OneLevelVLAN nor TwoLevelVLAN is active, the long frames are defined as more than 1522 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). If the TowLevelVLAN is active, then long frames are defined as more than 1538 octets (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

skGeConfEntriesNumber.name: skGeConfEntriesNumber
skGeConfEntriesNumber.description: The number of entries in the skGeConfTable.

skGeConfTable.name: skGeConfTable
skGeConfTable.description: The table describes the physical port data. The number of table entries is stored in skGeConfEntriesNumber.

skGeConfEntry.name: skGeConfEntry
skGeConfEntry.description: The first entry (skGeConfIndex) of each adapter card (skGeConfGeIndex) is a virtual one and represents the active MAC instance with settled statistical data. This means that the number of port specific statistical data entries in this table is by one element higher than the physically provided port number (skGePortNumber).

skGeConfGeIndex.name: skGeConfGeIndex
skGeConfGeIndex.description: Adapter index which corresponds with skGeIndex.

skGeConfIndex.name: skGeConfIndex
skGeConfIndex.description: The port index. The value is equivalent to skGeStatPortIndex. The ports are enumerated from 1..n. The first entry is the virtual one.

skGeConfPhysCurrentAddr.name: skGeConfPhysCurrentAddr
skGeConfPhysCurrentAddr.description: The physical address. The first entry of a adapter stores the physical address reported to the operating system. The other entries store the physical addresses of RLMT.

skGeConfPhysFactoryAddr.name: skGeConfPhysFactoryAddr
skGeConfPhysFactoryAddr.description: The burned in physical address. The first entry of a adapter stores the physical address reported to the operating system. The other entries store the physical addresses of RLMT.

skGeConfPMDType.name: skGeConfPMDType
skGeConfPMDType.description: Stores the physical media type of the port.

skGeConfConnector.name: skGeConfConnector
skGeConfConnector.description: Stores the connector type of the port.

skGeConfLinkCap.name: skGeConfLinkCap
skGeConfLinkCap.description: Indicates which connection modes the port supports. The modes are stored as a sum of powers of 2. Mode Power 0 half-duplex 1 full-duplex 2 auto-half-duplex 3 auto-full-duplex

skGeConfLinkMode.name: skGeConfLinkMode
skGeConfLinkMode.description: Defines in which mode the port should work. The modes half-duplex and full-duplex force the port to work in the corresponding mode. No autonegotiation is performed. The auto modes let the port perform autonegotiation with the capabilities half-duplex, full-duplex or both modes. The sense mode starts with autonegotiation and if failed falls back to full-duplex mode. After the link went down a new sense cycle is started.

skGeConfLinkModeStatus.name: skGeConfLinkModeStatus
skGeConfLinkModeStatus.description: Stores the mode with which the port is currently working. The keyword auto indicates that the link mode was established by autonegotiation. Otherwise the port was forced into the current mode.

skGeConfLinkStatus.name: skGeConfLinkStatus
skGeConfLinkStatus.description: Stores the link status of the unit. If a link becomes up or down a trap is generated.

skGeConfFlowCtrlCap.name: skGeConfFlowCtrlCap
skGeConfFlowCtrlCap.description: Indicates which flow control types the port supports.

skGeConfFlowCtrlMode.name: skGeConfFlowCtrlMode
skGeConfFlowCtrlMode.description: Defines the flow-control type the port should announce during auto-negotiation. If auto-negotiation is disabled flow-control is disabled and settings to this variable have no effect.

skGeConfFlowCtrlStatus.name: skGeConfFlowCtrlStatus
skGeConfFlowCtrlStatus.description: Stores the flow-control type the port is currently using.

skGeConfPhyOperationCap.name: skGeConfPhyOperationCap
skGeConfPhyOperationCap.description: Indicates which operation modes the phy supports. The modes are stored as a sum of powers of 2. Mode Power 0 master-slave auto-negotiation 1 master 2 slave

skGeConfPhyOperationMode.name: skGeConfPhyOperationMode
skGeConfPhyOperationMode.description: Defines in which mode the phy should work. The modes master and slave force the port to work in the corresponding mode. No autonegotiation is performed. The auto mode lets the port perform autonegotiation with the capabilities.

skGeConfPhyOperationStatus.name: skGeConfPhyOperationStatus
skGeConfPhyOperationStatus.description: Stores the operation mode with which the port is currently working.

skGeVpdTable.name: skGeVpdTable
skGeVpdTable.description: This table stores data for easy vpd access.

skGeVpdIndex.name: skGeVpdIndex
skGeVpdIndex.description: Adapter index that corresponds to skGeIndex.

skGeVpdFreeBytes.name: skGeVpdFreeBytes
skGeVpdFreeBytes.description: Stores the number of free bytes in the read-write area of the VPD RAM.

skGeVpdEntryList.name: skGeVpdEntryList
skGeVpdEntryList.description: Stores a list of the VPD keywords. The elements of the list are separated by a space character (0x20).

skGeVpdValueTable.name: skGeVpdValueTable
skGeVpdValueTable.description: This table provides access to the Vital Product Data (VPD).

skGeVpdValueEntry.name: skGeVpdValueEntry
skGeVpdValueEntry.description: VPD value table entry. On creation of a new entry: If the key is first set the vpd subsystem will create a new entry with an empty value field. If the value is first set the key must extracted from the oid and key a nd value are then set simultaneously.

skGeVpdValueIndex.name: skGeVpdValueIndex
skGeVpdValueIndex.description: Adapter index that corresponds to skGeIndex.

skGeVpdAccess.name: skGeVpdAccess
skGeVpdAccess.description: Defines whether the entry is only readable or also writable. Read-only entries cannot be changed or deleted.

skGeVpdValid.name: skGeVpdValid
skGeVpdValid.description: If the entry is writeable a set to 'invalid' will remove the entry from the VPD. A set to 'valid' will have no effect.

skGeRlmtEntriesNumber.name: skGeRlmtEntriesNumber
skGeRlmtEntriesNumber.description: Stores the number of skGeRlmtTable entries. The number corresponds to skGeNumber.

skGeRlmtTable.name: skGeRlmtTable
skGeRlmtTable.description: Table for RLMT (Redundant Link ManagemenT) specific data.

skGeRlmtIndex.name: skGeRlmtIndex
skGeRlmtIndex.description: Stores the index of the adapter card that corresponds with this entry. It is identical to skGeIndex.

skGeRlmtMode.name: skGeRlmtMode
skGeRlmtMode.description: Stores the working mode of RLMT as a power of 2. Mode Power link-check 0 Always active send-check 1 Sends hello packets spanning-tree 2 Monitors SP packets monitor 3 Monitors other GE-NICs

skGeRlmtPortActive.name: skGeRlmtPortActive
skGeRlmtPortActive.description: Stores the index of the currently active port. The value 0 indicates that currently no port is active.

skGeRlmtPortPreferred.name: skGeRlmtPortPreferred
